# Tasks: Stage 0 Complete Compiler

**Input**: Design documents from `/specs/045-stage0-complete-compiler/`
**Prerequisites**: plan.md, spec.md, research.md, data-model.md, contracts/

**Tests**: TDD required per Constitution (Principle VII). Tests written first, must fail before implementation.

**Organization**: Tasks grouped by user story. Note: US4 and US5 (P2) are foundational prerequisites for P1 stories.

## Format: `[ID] [P?] [Story] Description`

- **[P]**: Can run in parallel (different files, no dependencies)
- **[Story]**: Which user story (US1-US5)
- Paths use single project structure: `src/`, `tests/`, `build/`, `scripts/`

---

## Phase 1: Setup (Shared Infrastructure)

**Purpose**: Project initialization and directory structure

- [X] T001 Create src/clysm/stage0/ directory structure per plan.md
- [X] T002 [P] Create src/clysm/stage0/package.lisp with CLYSM-STAGE0 package definition
- [X] T003 [P] Create tests/unit/stage0/ directory for unit tests
- [X] T004 [P] Create tests/contract/stage0/ directory for contract tests
- [X] T005 [P] Create tests/integration/stage0/ directory for integration tests
- [X] T006 Update clysm.asd with :clysm/stage0 system definition

---

## Phase 2: Foundational (Blocking Prerequisites)

**Purpose**: Core infrastructure required by ALL user stories

**⚠️ CRITICAL**: This includes US4 (Runtime Initialization) and US5 (Read Source Files) because they are prerequisites for all P1 stories.

### US4: Runtime Initialization Infrastructure

- [X] T007 [P] [US4] Unit test: WasmGC type section generation in tests/unit/stage0/types-test.lisp
- [X] T008 [P] [US4] Unit test: Global variable initialization in tests/unit/stage0/globals-test.lisp
- [X] T009 [P] [US4] Contract test: Wasm module validates in tests/contract/stage0/runtime-valid-test.lisp
- [X] T010 [US4] Implement WasmGC type definitions (24+ types) in src/clysm/stage0/types.lisp
- [X] T011 [US4] Implement global variable initialization in src/clysm/stage0/globals.lisp
- [X] T012 [US4] Implement _initialize export function in src/clysm/stage0/runtime.lisp
- [X] T013 [US4] Implement start function for auto-init in src/clysm/stage0/runtime.lisp

### US5: FFI Filesystem Access Infrastructure

- [X] T014 [P] [US5] Unit test: FFI import declarations in tests/unit/stage0/ffi-test.lisp
- [X] T015 [P] [US5] Unit test: File reading in tests/unit/stage0/fs-read-test.lisp
- [X] T016 [P] [US5] Contract test: FFI imports valid in tests/contract/stage0/ffi-valid-test.lisp
- [X] T017 [US5] Implement FFI import declarations (fs.open, fs.read-all, fs.write-all, fs.close) in src/clysm/stage0/ffi.lisp

- [X] T020 [US5] Update host-shim/stage1-host.js with clysm.fs FFI implementations (fs-shim.js exists)

### Core Compiler Infrastructure (shared)

- [X] T021 [P] Unit test: S-expression reading in tests/unit/stage0/reader-test.lisp
- [X] T022 [P] Unit test: AST parsing in tests/unit/stage0/ast-test.lisp
- [X] T023 [P] Unit test: Wasm IR generation in tests/unit/stage0/ir-test.lisp
- [X] T024 Implement S-expression reader (cross-compiled) in src/clysm/stage0/reader.lisp
- [X] T025 Implement AST parser (cross-compiled) in src/clysm/stage0/ast.lisp
- [X] T026 Implement Wasm IR generator (cross-compiled) in src/clysm/stage0/ir.lisp
- [X] T027 Implement Wasm binary emitter (cross-compiled) in src/clysm/stage0/codegen.lisp

**Checkpoint**: Foundation ready - Stage 0 can be instantiated with types, globals, and FFI

---

## Phase 3: User Story 1 - Compile Simple Expression via CLI (Priority: P1) 🎯 MVP

**Goal**: Run `wasmtime run clysm-stage0.wasm --invoke compile_form '(+ 1 2)'` successfully

**Independent Test**: Execute compile_form with arithmetic expression and verify valid Wasm output

### Tests for User Story 1

### Verification for User Story 1

- [X] T039 [US1] Run: `wasm-tools validate dist/clysm-stage0.wasm` - Known limitation: type mismatch in global init
- [ ] T040 [US1] Run: `wasmtime run dist/clysm-stage0.wasm --invoke compile_form '(+ 1 2)'` - Blocked by T039
- [ ] T041 [US1] Validate compiled output with wasm-tools - Blocked by T039

**Checkpoint**: MVP complete - Stage 0 can compile single expressions

---

## Phase 4: User Story 2 - Compile Clysm Source to Stage 1 (Priority: P1)

**Goal**: Stage 0 compiles all 45 source modules to produce valid Stage 1 binary

**Independent Test**: Run compile_all and verify dist/clysm-stage1.wasm passes validation

### Tests for User Story 2

- [ ] T042 [P] [US2] Contract test: compile_all export exists in tests/contract/stage0/exports-test.lisp
- [ ] T043 [P] [US2] Integration test: Compile single module in tests/integration/stage0/module-test.lisp
- [ ] T044 [P] [US2] Integration test: Compile all modules in tests/integration/stage0/compile-all-test.lisp
- [ ] T045 [P] [US2] Integration test: Graceful degradation on unsupported form in tests/integration/stage0/graceful-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 2

- [ ] T046 [US2] Implement compile_all function signature in src/clysm/stage0/entry.lisp
- [ ] T047 [US2] Implement module path list from compiler-order.lisp in src/clysm/stage0/modules.lisp
- [ ] T048 [US2] Implement module loading via FFI in src/clysm/stage0/loader.lisp
- [ ] T049 [US2] Implement per-form compilation loop in src/clysm/stage0/compiler.lisp
- [ ] T050 [US2] Implement Wasm section accumulation in src/clysm/stage0/codegen.lisp
- [ ] T051 [US2] Implement progress reporting via FFI in src/clysm/stage0/progress.lisp
- [ ] T052 [US2] Implement graceful degradation for unsupported forms in src/clysm/stage0/compiler.lisp
- [ ] T053 [US2] Implement Stage 1 binary output via FFI in src/clysm/stage0/output.lisp
- [ ] T054 [US2] Export compile_all in Wasm export section in src/clysm/stage0/exports.lisp

### Verification for User Story 2

- [ ] T055 [US2] Run: `node host-shim/stage1-host.js --stage0 dist/clysm-stage0.wasm` - verify Stage 1 generated
- [ ] T056 [US2] Run: `wasm-tools validate dist/clysm-stage1.wasm` - verify exits 0
- [ ] T057 [US2] Verify Stage 1 exports compile_form and compile_all

**Checkpoint**: Stage 0 can self-compile to produce Stage 1

---

## Phase 5: User Story 3 - Achieve Fixed-Point (Stage 1 == Stage 2) (Priority: P1)

**Goal**: Stage 1 compiles Clysm to Stage 2, and Stage 1 == Stage 2 byte-identical

**Independent Test**: Run `./scripts/verify-fixpoint.sh` and verify exit 0

### Tests for User Story 3

- [ ] T058 [P] [US3] Integration test: Stage 2 generation in tests/integration/stage0/stage2-gen-test.lisp
- [ ] T059 [P] [US3] Integration test: Binary comparison in tests/integration/stage0/binary-cmp-test.lisp
- [ ] T060 [P] [US3] Integration test: Full fixpoint verification in tests/integration/stage0/fixpoint-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 3

- [ ] T061 [US3] Extend scripts/verify-fixpoint.sh to use complete Stage 0
- [ ] T062 [US3] Implement Stage 2 generation in scripts/run-stage2-gen.sh
- [ ] T063 [US3] Implement byte-by-byte comparison in src/clysm/stage2/verifier.lisp
- [ ] T064 [US3] Implement first-diff-offset reporting in src/clysm/stage2/verifier.lisp
- [ ] T065 [US3] Implement verification-history.jsonl logging in src/clysm/stage2/verifier.lisp
- [ ] T066 [US3] Ensure deterministic compilation (no timestamps/random) in src/clysm/stage0/codegen.lisp

### Verification for User Story 3

- [ ] T067 [US3] Run: Stage 1 generates Stage 2 successfully
- [ ] T068 [US3] Run: `wasm-tools validate dist/clysm-stage2.wasm` - verify exits 0
- [ ] T069 [US3] Run: `./scripts/verify-fixpoint.sh` - verify exits 0 (ACHIEVED)
- [ ] T070 [US3] Verify dist/verification-history.jsonl contains success record

**Checkpoint**: Fixed-point achieved - Clysm is self-hosting

---

## Phase 6: Polish & Cross-Cutting Concerns

**Purpose**: Improvements affecting multiple user stories

- [ ] T071 [P] Update CLAUDE.md with Feature 045 documentation
- [ ] T072 [P] Update docs/blessed-subset.lisp if new features added
- [ ] T073 Code cleanup: Remove dead code from stage0 modules
- [ ] T074 Performance: Profile Stage 1 generation, optimize bottlenecks
- [ ] T075 [P] Add verbose logging mode to build/stage0-complete.lisp
- [ ] T076 [P] Add --help to host-shim/stage1-host.js
- [ ] T077 Verify quickstart.md instructions work end-to-end
- [ ] T078 Run all rove tests: `sbcl --eval '(rove:run :clysm/tests/stage0)'`

---

## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies

```
Phase 1: Setup
    ↓
Phase 2: Foundational (US4 Runtime + US5 FFI + Core)
    ↓ (BLOCKS ALL P1 STORIES)
    ├── Phase 3: US1 - Compile Simple Expression (MVP)
    │       ↓
    ├── Phase 4: US2 - Compile Clysm to Stage 1
    │       ↓
    └── Phase 5: US3 - Fixed-Point Verification
            ↓
Phase 6: Polish
```

### User Story Dependencies

| Story | Depends On | Can Start After |
|-------|------------|-----------------|
| US4 (Runtime) | Setup | Phase 1 complete |
| US5 (FFI) | Setup | Phase 1 complete |
| US1 (Compile Form) | US4, Core | Phase 2 complete |
| US2 (Compile All) | US1, US5 | Phase 3 complete |
| US3 (Fixed-Point) | US2 | Phase 4 complete |

### Within Each Phase

1. Tests MUST be written and FAIL before implementation
2. Contract tests before unit tests (verify structure)
3. Core implementation before exports
4. Verification tasks last

### Parallel Opportunities

**Phase 2 (Foundational)**: These task groups can run in parallel:
- T007-T009 (US4 tests) in parallel
- T014-T016 (US5 tests) in parallel
- T021-T023 (Core tests) in parallel

**Phase 3 (US1)**: These can run in parallel:
- T028-T031 (all tests)

**Phase 4 (US2)**: These can run in parallel:
- T042-T045 (all tests)

**Phase 5 (US3)**: These can run in parallel:
- T058-T060 (all tests)

---

## Parallel Example: Phase 2 Foundational

```bash
# Launch all US4 tests in parallel:
Task: "Unit test: WasmGC type section generation in tests/unit/stage0/types-test.lisp"
Task: "Unit test: Global variable initialization in tests/unit/stage0/globals-test.lisp"
Task: "Contract test: Wasm module validates in tests/contract/stage0/runtime-valid-test.lisp"

# Launch all US5 tests in parallel:
Task: "Unit test: FFI import declarations in tests/unit/stage0/ffi-test.lisp"
Task: "Unit test: File reading in tests/unit/stage0/fs-read-test.lisp"
Task: "Contract test: FFI imports valid in tests/contract/stage0/ffi-valid-test.lisp"
```

---

## Implementation Strategy

### MVP First (User Story 1 Only)

1. Complete Phase 1: Setup (T001-T006)
2. Complete Phase 2: Foundational (T007-T027) - **BLOCKING**
3. Complete Phase 3: User Story 1 (T028-T041)
4. **STOP and VALIDATE**: `wasmtime run dist/clysm-stage0.wasm --invoke compile_form '(+ 1 2)'`
5. Celebrate: Stage 0 can compile expressions!

### Full Self-Hosting

1. Complete MVP (Phases 1-3)
2. Complete Phase 4: User Story 2 (T042-T057)
3. **VALIDATE**: Stage 1 is valid Wasm
4. Complete Phase 5: User Story 3 (T058-T070)
5. **VALIDATE**: `./scripts/verify-fixpoint.sh` exits 0
6. Complete Phase 6: Polish
7. **FINAL**: Clysm is self-hosting!

### Success Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measured By |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| compile_form works | exit 0 | wasmtime --invoke |
| Stage 1 valid | exit 0 | wasm-tools validate |
| Stage 2 valid | exit 0 | wasm-tools validate |
| Fixed-point | exit 0 | verify-fixpoint.sh |
| Binary size | < 5MB | ls -la dist/clysm-stage0.wasm |
| Verification time | < 5 min | time ./scripts/verify-fixpoint.sh |

---

## Notes

- [P] = parallelizable (different files, no dependencies)
- [US#] = maps to user story for traceability
- Constitution requires TDD: tests MUST fail before implementation
- Each checkpoint validates independent functionality
- Use `wasm-tools validate` after every codegen change
- Commit after each logical task group

1→;;;; globals.lisp - Global variable initialization for Stage 0 complete compiler
     2→;;;;
     3→;;;; Part of Feature 045: Stage 0 Complete Compiler
     4→;;;; Implements US4: Runtime Initialization - Global variable initialization
     5→;;;;
     6→;;;; This file generates the global section for Stage 0 Wasm binary,
     7→;;;; defining and initializing the required global variables:
     8→;;;; - NIL (index 0): The empty list / false value singleton
     9→;;;; - UNBOUND (index 1): Sentinel for unbound variable slots
    10→;;;; - mv-count (index 2): Multiple values count
    11→;;;; - mv-buffer (index 3): Multiple values buffer array
    12→
    13→(in-package #:clysm/stage0)
    14→
    15→;;; ============================================================
    16→;;; Global Indices (exported for use by other modules)
    17→;;; ============================================================
    18→
    19→(defvar *nil-index* 0 "Global index for NIL singleton")
    20→(defvar *unbound-index* 1 "Global index for UNBOUND sentinel")
    21→(defvar *mv-count-index* 2 "Global index for multiple values count")
    22→(defvar *mv-buffer-index* 3 "Global index for multiple values buffer")
    23→
    24→(defconstant +total-globals+ 4 "Total number of global variables")
    25→
    26→;;; ============================================================
    27→;;; Wasm Instruction Encoding Constants
    28→;;; ============================================================
    29→
    30→;; Control instructions
    31→(defconstant +end+ #x0B)
    32→
    33→;; Constant instructions
    34→(defconstant +i32-const+ #x41)
    35→(defconstant +i64-const+ #x42)
    36→(defconstant +f64-const+ #x44)
    37→
    38→;; Reference instructions
    39→(defconstant +ref-null+ #xD0)
    40→
    41→;; GC instructions (prefixed with #xFB)
    42→(defconstant +struct-new+ #x00)       ; struct.new $type
    43→(defconstant +struct-new-default+ #x01) ; struct.new_default $type
    44→(defconstant +array-new+ #x06)        ; array.new $type
    45→(defconstant +array-new-default+ #x07) ; array.new_default $type
    46→(defconstant +array-new-fixed+ #x08)  ; array.new_fixed $type $len
    47→
    48→;;; ============================================================
    49→;;; Global Type Definitions
    50→;;; ============================================================
    51→
    52→(defun global-nil-type ()
    53→  "Return type bytes for NIL global: (ref $nil)"
    54→  ;; ref $nil is a non-nullable reference to struct type 0
    55→  (list +non-null+ +type-nil+))
    56→
    57→(defun global-unbound-type ()
    58→  "Return type bytes for UNBOUND global: (ref $unbound)"
    59→  (list +non-null+ +type-unbound+))
    60→
    61→(defun global-mv-count-type ()
    62→  "Return type bytes for mv-count global: i32"
    63→  (list +wasm-i32+))
    64→
    65→(defun global-mv-buffer-type ()
    66→  "Return type bytes for mv-buffer global: (ref $mv_array)"
    67→  (list +non-null+ +type-mv-array+))
    68→
    69→;;; ============================================================
    70→;;; Global Initialization Expressions
    71→;;; ============================================================
    72→
    73→(defun init-nil-global ()
    74→  "Generate initialization expression for NIL global.
    75→   Creates NIL singleton using struct.new_default."
    76→  ;; struct.new_default $nil
    77→  (list +gc-prefix+ +struct-new-default+ +type-nil+ +end+))
    78→
    79→(defun init-unbound-global ()
    80→  "Generate initialization expression for UNBOUND global.
    81→   Creates UNBOUND sentinel using struct.new_default."
    82→  ;; struct.new_default $unbound
    83→  (list +gc-prefix+ +struct-new-default+ +type-unbound+ +end+))
    84→
    85→(defun init-mv-count-global ()
    86→  "Generate initialization expression for mv-count global.
    87→   Initializes to 1 (single value return is default)."
    88→  ;; i32.const 1
    89→  (list +i32-const+ 1 +end+))
    90→
    91→(defun init-mv-buffer-global ()
    92→  "Generate initialization expression for mv-buffer global.
    93→   Creates empty array of size 20 (MAX_VALUES)."
    94→  ;; array.new_default $mv_array 20
    95→  (list +gc-prefix+ +array-new-default+ +type-mv-array+
    96→        +i32-const+ 20 +end+))  ; Create array of 20 slots
    97→
    98→;;; ============================================================
    99→;;; Global Section Generation
   100→;;; ============================================================
   101→
   102→(defun encode-global (type-bytes mutability init-bytes)
   103→  "Encode a single global definition.
   104→   Returns list of bytes for: valtype mut init_expr"
   105→  (append type-bytes
   106→          (list mutability)
   107→          init-bytes))
   108→
   109→(defun generate-all-globals ()
   110→  "Generate list of all global definitions in order.
   111→   Each global is: (type-bytes mutability init-bytes)"
   112→  (list
   113→   ;; Global 0: NIL - immutable
   114→   (encode-global (global-nil-type) +immutable+ (init-nil-global))
   115→   ;; Global 1: UNBOUND - immutable
   116→   (encode-global (global-unbound-type) +immutable+ (init-unbound-global))
   117→   ;; Global 2: mv-count - mutable
   118→   (encode-global (global-mv-count-type) +mutable+ (init-mv-count-global))
   119→   ;; Global 3: mv-buffer - mutable
   120→   (encode-global (global-mv-buffer-type) +mutable+ (init-mv-buffer-global))))
   121→
   122→(defun generate-global-section ()
   123→  "Generate complete global section as byte vector.
   124→   Returns vector of bytes for Wasm global section (section ID 6)."
   125→  (let* ((globals (generate-all-globals))
   126→         (global-bytes '())
   127→         (global-count (length globals)))
   128→    ;; Encode each global definition
   129→    (dolist (global-def globals)
   130→      (dolist (byte global-def)
   131→        (push byte global-bytes)))
   132→    ;; Reverse to get correct order
   133→    (setf global-bytes (nreverse global-bytes))
   134→    ;; Build section: ID + size + count + global definitions
   135→    (let* ((count-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 global-count))
   136→           (content-size (+ (length count-bytes) (length global-bytes)))
   137→           (size-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 content-size))
   138→           (section '()))
   139→      ;; Section ID 6 (global)
   140→      (push 6 section)
   141→      ;; Section size
   142→      (dolist (b size-bytes) (push b section))
   143→      ;; Global count
   144→      (dolist (b count-bytes) (push b section))
   145→      ;; Global definitions

;;;; globals.lisp - Global variable initialization for Stage 0 complete compiler
;;;;
;;;; Part of Feature 045: Stage 0 Complete Compiler
;;;; Implements US4: Runtime Initialization - Global variable initialization
;;;;
;;;; This file generates the global section for Stage 0 Wasm binary,
;;;; defining and initializing the required global variables:
;;;; - NIL (index 0): The empty list / false value singleton
;;;; - UNBOUND (index 1): Sentinel for unbound variable slots
;;;; - mv-count (index 2): Multiple values count
;;;; - mv-buffer (index 3): Multiple values buffer array

(in-package #:clysm/stage0)

;;; ============================================================
;;; Global Indices (exported for use by other modules)
;;; ============================================================

(defvar *nil-index* 0 "Global index for NIL singleton")
(defvar *unbound-index* 1 "Global index for UNBOUND sentinel")
(defvar *mv-count-index* 2 "Global index for multiple values count")
(defvar *mv-buffer-index* 3 "Global index for multiple values buffer")

(defconstant +total-globals+ 4 "Total number of global variables")

;;; ============================================================
;;; Wasm Instruction Encoding Constants
;;; ============================================================

;; Control instructions
(defconstant +end+ #x0B)

;; Constant instructions
(defconstant +i32-const+ #x41)
(defconstant +i64-const+ #x42)
(defconstant +f64-const+ #x44)

;; Reference instructions
(defconstant +ref-null+ #xD0)

;; GC instructions (prefixed with #xFB)
(defconstant +struct-new+ #x00)       ; struct.new $type
(defconstant +struct-new-default+ #x01) ; struct.new_default $type
(defconstant +array-new+ #x06)        ; array.new $type
(defconstant +array-new-default+ #x07) ; array.new_default $type
(defconstant +array-new-fixed+ #x08)  ; array.new_fixed $type $len

;;; ============================================================
;;; Global Type Definitions
;;; ============================================================

(defun global-nil-type ()
  "Return type bytes for NIL global: (ref $nil)"
  ;; ref $nil is a non-nullable reference to struct type 0
  (list +non-null+ +type-nil+))

(defun global-unbound-type ()
  "Return type bytes for UNBOUND global: (ref $unbound)"
  (list +non-null+ +type-unbound+))

(defun global-mv-count-type ()
  "Return type bytes for mv-count global: i32"
  (list +wasm-i32+))

(defun global-mv-buffer-type ()
  "Return type bytes for mv-buffer global: (ref $mv_array)"
  (list +non-null+ +type-mv-array+))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Global Initialization Expressions
;;; ============================================================

(defun init-nil-global ()
  "Generate initialization expression for NIL global.
   Creates NIL singleton using struct.new_default."
  ;; struct.new_default $nil
  (list +gc-prefix+ +struct-new-default+ +type-nil+ +end+))

(defun init-unbound-global ()
  "Generate initialization expression for UNBOUND global.
   Creates UNBOUND sentinel using struct.new_default."
  ;; struct.new_default $unbound
  (list +gc-prefix+ +struct-new-default+ +type-unbound+ +end+))

(defun init-mv-count-global ()
  "Generate initialization expression for mv-count global.
   Initializes to 1 (single value return is default)."
  ;; i32.const 1
  (list +i32-const+ 1 +end+))

(defun init-mv-buffer-global ()
  "Generate initialization expression for mv-buffer global.
   Creates empty array of size 20 (MAX_VALUES)."
  ;; array.new_default $mv_array 20
  (list +gc-prefix+ +array-new-default+ +type-mv-array+
        +i32-const+ 20 +end+))  ; Create array of 20 slots

;;; ============================================================
;;; Global Section Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun encode-global (type-bytes mutability init-bytes)
  "Encode a single global definition.
   Returns list of bytes for: valtype mut init_expr"
  (append type-bytes
          (list mutability)
          init-bytes))

(defun generate-all-globals ()
  "Generate list of all global definitions in order.
   Each global is: (type-bytes mutability init-bytes)"
  (list
   ;; Global 0: NIL - immutable
   (encode-global (global-nil-type) +immutable+ (init-nil-global))
   ;; Global 1: UNBOUND - immutable
   (encode-global (global-unbound-type) +immutable+ (init-unbound-global))
   ;; Global 2: mv-count - mutable
   (encode-global (global-mv-count-type) +mutable+ (init-mv-count-global))
   ;; Global 3: mv-buffer - mutable
   (encode-global (global-mv-buffer-type) +mutable+ (init-mv-buffer-global))))

(defun generate-global-section ()
  "Generate complete global section as byte vector.
   Returns vector of bytes for Wasm global section (section ID 6)."
  (let* ((globals (generate-all-globals))
         (global-bytes '())
         (global-count (length globals)))
    ;; Encode each global definition
    (dolist (global-def globals)
      (dolist (byte global-def)
        (push byte global-bytes)))
    ;; Reverse to get correct order
    (setf global-bytes (nreverse global-bytes))
    ;; Build section: ID + size + count + global definitions
    (let* ((count-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 global-count))
           (content-size (+ (length count-bytes) (length global-bytes)))
           (size-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 content-size))
           (section '()))
      ;; Section ID 6 (global)
      (push 6 section)
      ;; Section size
      (dolist (b size-bytes) (push b section))
      ;; Global count
      (dolist (b count-bytes) (push b section))
      ;; Global definitions
      (dolist (b global-bytes) (push b section))
      ;; Return as byte vector
      (coerce (nreverse section) '(vector (unsigned-byte 8))))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Global Initialization Instructions (for start function)
;;; ============================================================

(defun generate-global-init ()
  "Generate instructions for initializing globals in start function.
   Returns list of instruction forms for the compiler.

   Note: Most globals use init expressions in the global section,
   but some complex initialization may need to happen in the start
   function. This returns any additional initialization needed."
  ;; Currently, all globals can be initialized in their definition
  ;; This function is here for future extensibility
  '())

content.thinking:
The error is "type mismatch: expected i32 but nothing on stack (at offset 0xc7)". Looking at the globals.lisp, I see the issue in `init-mv-buffer-global`:

```lisp
(defun init-mv-buffer-global ()
  "Generate initialization expression for mv-buffer global.
   Creates empty array of size 20 (MAX_VALUES)."
  ;; array.new_default $mv_array 20
  (list +gc-prefix+ +array-new-default+ +type-mv-array+
        +i32-const+ 20 +end+))  ; Create array of 20 slots
```

The problem is the order of instructions. For `array.new_default`, the size argument needs to be on the stack BEFORE the instruction. So it should be:

```
i32.const 20    ; push size on stack
array.new_default $mv_array  ; consumes the size
end
```

But the code has:
```
array.new_default $mv_array  ; ERROR: expects size but nothing on stack
i32.const 20    ; too late
end
```

Let me fix this. The i32.const 20 needs to come BEFORE the array.new_default instruction.

;;;; runtime.lisp - Runtime initialization for Stage 0 complete compiler
;;;;
;;;; Part of Feature 045: Stage 0 Complete Compiler
;;;; Implements US4: Runtime Initialization
;;;;
;;;; T012: Implement _initialize export function
;;;; T013: Implement start function for auto-init
;;;;
;;;; This file generates the complete runtime initialization for Stage 0,
;;;; combining type section, global section, and start function.

(in-package #:clysm/stage0)

;;; ============================================================
;;; Wasm Module Structure Constants
;;; ============================================================

;; Wasm magic number: \0asm
(defparameter *wasm-magic* '(#x00 #x61 #x73 #x6D))

;; Wasm version 1.0
(defparameter *wasm-version* '(#x01 #x00 #x00 #x00))

;; Note: Section IDs are defined in types.lisp

;;; ============================================================
;;; Function Section Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun generate-empty-function-section ()
  "Generate an empty function section (no user functions initially)."
  ;; Section ID 3, size 1, count 0
  (coerce '(3 1 0) '(vector (unsigned-byte 8))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Start Function Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defvar *start-function-index* nil
  "Index of the start function in the function section")

(defun generate-start-function ()
  "Generate start function body for auto-initialization.
   The start function runs automatically when the module is instantiated.
   Returns list of instructions."
  ;; Start function currently just returns (no additional init needed)
  ;; All initialization happens in global init expressions
  (list +end+))

(defun generate-start-section (start-func-index)
  "Generate start section pointing to the start function.
   Returns byte vector for Wasm start section (section ID 8)."
  (let* ((index-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 start-func-index))
         (size-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 (length index-bytes)))
         (section '()))
    ;; Section ID 8
    (push +section-start+ section)
    ;; Section size
    (dolist (b size-bytes) (push b section))
    ;; Function index
    (dolist (b index-bytes) (push b section))
    (coerce (nreverse section) '(vector (unsigned-byte 8)))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Code Section Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun generate-empty-code-section ()
  "Generate an empty code section."
  ;; Section ID 10, size 1, count 0
  (coerce '(10 1 0) '(vector (unsigned-byte 8))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Export Section Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun encode-name (name)
  "Encode a name as UTF-8 bytes with length prefix."
  (let* ((bytes (map 'list #'char-code name))
         (len-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 (length bytes))))
    (append len-bytes bytes)))

(defun generate-initialize-export (func-index)
  "Generate export entry for _initialize function."
  (append (encode-name "_initialize")
          (list #x00)  ; export kind: func
          (encode-unsigned-leb128 func-index)))

(defun generate-export-section (exports)
  "Generate export section for given export list.
   Each export is (name kind index).
   Returns byte vector for Wasm export section (section ID 7)."
  (let* ((export-bytes '())
         (export-count (length exports)))
    ;; Encode each export
    (dolist (export exports)
      (destructuring-bind (name kind index) export
        (dolist (b (encode-name name))
          (push b export-bytes))
        (push kind export-bytes)
        (dolist (b (encode-unsigned-leb128 index))
          (push b export-bytes))))
    (setf export-bytes (nreverse export-bytes))
    ;; Build section
    (let* ((count-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 export-count))
           (content-size (+ (length count-bytes) (length export-bytes)))
           (size-bytes (encode-unsigned-leb128 content-size))
           (section '()))
      (push +section-export+ section)
      (dolist (b size-bytes) (push b section))
      (dolist (b count-bytes) (push b section))
      (dolist (b export-bytes) (push b section))
      (coerce (nreverse section) '(vector (unsigned-byte 8))))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Complete Runtime Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun concatenate-byte-vectors (&rest vectors)
  "Concatenate multiple byte vectors into one."
  (let* ((total-length (reduce #'+ vectors :key #'length))
         (result (make-array total-length
                             :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
                             :initial-element 0))
         (pos 0))
    (dolist (vec vectors)
      (loop for byte across vec
            do (setf (aref result pos) byte)
               (incf pos)))
    result))

(defun generate-runtime-init ()
  "Generate complete runtime initialization as Wasm module.
   Returns byte vector containing:
   - Wasm magic number and version
   - Type section (all WasmGC types)
   - Global section (NIL, UNBOUND, mv-count, mv-buffer)
   - Export section (_initialize export)

   This creates a minimal valid Wasm module for Stage 0 runtime."
  (let* (;; Generate sections
         (header (coerce (append *wasm-magic* *wasm-version*)
                         '(vector (unsigned-byte 8))))
         (type-section (generate-type-section))
         (global-section (generate-global-section))
         ;; For minimal runtime, we export the runtime as available
         ;; The actual _initialize will be added when we have functions
         (export-section (generate-export-section '())))
    ;; Concatenate all sections in order
    (concatenate-byte-vectors
     header
     type-section
     global-section
     export-section)))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Full Stage 0 Module Generation
;;; ============================================================

(defun generate-stage0-module ()
  "Generate complete Stage 0 Wasm module with all sections.
   This is used when building the full compiler binary."
  ;; For now, return runtime init
  ;; Will be extended when compile_form and compile_all are implemented
  (generate-runtime-init))

;;;; entry.lisp - Entry points for Stage 0 complete compiler
;;;;
;;;; Part of Feature 045: Stage 0 Complete Compiler
;;;; Implements compile_form and compile_all exported functions
;;;;
;;;; These are the main entry points that wasmtime calls.

(in-package #:clysm/stage0)

;;; ============================================================
;;; compile_form - Compile a Single Expression (US1)
;;; ============================================================

(defun compile-form (source-string)
  "Compile a single Lisp expression to Wasm bytes.
   This is the main entry point for single-form compilation.

   Args:
     source-string: String containing Lisp expression, e.g. \"(+ 1 2)\"

   Returns:
     stage0-result struct with:
       - success-p: T if compilation succeeded
       - wasm-bytes: Vector of Wasm bytes (if success)
       - error-message: Error description (if failure)
       - form-count: Number of forms compiled (usually 1)

   Example:
     (compile-form \"(+ 1 2)\")
     => #S(stage0-result :success-p T :wasm-bytes #(...) :form-count 1)"
  (clear-progress-log)
  (handler-case
      (let* ((forms (read-source-string source-string))
             (compiled (compile-forms forms))
             (exports (generate-exports))
             (wasm-bytes (emit-stage0-module compiled exports)))
        (if (validate-wasm-bytes wasm-bytes)
            (make-stage0-result
             :success-p t
             :wasm-bytes wasm-bytes
             :form-count (length forms))
            (make-stage0-result
             :success-p nil
             :error-message "Generated Wasm failed validation"
             :form-count (length forms))))
    (error (e)
      (make-stage0-result
       :success-p nil
       :error-message (format nil "~A" e)
       :form-count 0))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; compile_all - Compile All Modules (US2)
;;; ============================================================

(defun compile-all (&key (output-path *output-path*))
  "Compile all Clysm source modules to produce Stage 1 binary.
   This is the main entry point for full compilation.

   Args:
     output-path: Path for output binary (default: dist/clysm-stage1.wasm)

   Returns:
     stage0-result struct with:
       - success-p: T if compilation succeeded
       - wasm-bytes: Vector of Wasm bytes (if success)
       - error-message: Error description (if failure)
       - form-count: Total number of forms compiled

   Example:
     (compile-all)
     => #S(stage0-result :success-p T :wasm-bytes #(...) :form-count 900)"
  (clear-progress-log)
  (handler-case
      (let* (;; Load all modules
             (modules (load-all-modules))
             ;; Compile all forms with graceful degradation
             (compiled (mapcan #'compile-module-with-degradation modules))
             ;; Generate exports
             (exports (generate-exports))
             ;; Emit final binary
             (wasm-bytes (emit-stage0-module compiled exports)))
        ;; Validate and write output
        (if (validate-wasm-bytes wasm-bytes)
            (progn
              (write-stage1-binary wasm-bytes :path output-path)
              (make-stage0-result
               :success-p t
               :wasm-bytes wasm-bytes
               :form-count (length compiled)))
            (make-stage0-result
             :success-p nil
             :error-message "Generated Wasm failed validation"
             :form-count (length compiled))))
    (error (e)
      (make-stage0-result
       :success-p nil
       :error-message (format nil "~A" e)
       :form-count 0))))

;;; ============================================================
;;; CLI Entry Point
;;; ============================================================

(defun main (&optional args)
  "Main entry point for CLI invocation.
   Called when wasmtime runs the Stage 0 binary.

   Args:
     args: Command-line arguments

   Usage:
     wasmtime run dist/clysm-stage0.wasm --invoke compile_form '(+ 1 2)'
     wasmtime run dist/clysm-stage0.wasm --invoke compile_all"
  (cond
    ;; No args - compile all
    ((null args)
     (let ((result (compile-all)))
       (if (stage0-result-success-p result)
           (format t "~&Success: Compiled ~D forms~%"
                   (stage0-result-form-count result))
           (format t "~&Error: ~A~%"
                   (stage0-result-error-message result)))
       (if (stage0-result-success-p result) 0 1)))

    ;; Single expression
    ((stringp (first args))
     (let ((result (compile-form (first args))))
       (if (stage0-result-success-p result)
           (format t "~&Success: Compiled ~D form(s)~%"
                   (stage0-result-form-count result))
           (format t "~&Error: ~A~%"
                   (stage0-result-error-message result)))
       (if (stage0-result-success-p result) 0 1)))

    (t
     (format t "~&Usage: compile_form <expression> | compile_all~%")
     1)))

;;;; exports.lisp - Wasm exports for Stage 0 complete compiler
;;;;
;;;; Part of Feature 045: Stage 0 Complete Compiler
;;;; Defines the export section for Stage 0

(in-package #:clysm/stage0)

;;; ============================================================
;;; Export Registry
;;; ============================================================

(defvar *exported-functions* '()
  "List of exported function entries: (name func-index)")

(defun register-export (name func-index)
  "Register a function for export"
  (push (list name func-index) *exported-functions*))

(defun clear-exports ()
  "Clear export registry"
  (setf *exported-functions* nil))

;;; ============================================================
;;; Standard Exports
;;; ============================================================

(defun generate-exports ()
  "Generate export list for Stage 0.
   Returns list of (name kind index) suitable for emit-export-section."
  ;; Standard Stage 0 exports:
  ;; - compile_form: Compile a single form (index will be assigned)
  ;; - compile_all: Compile all modules (index will be assigned)
  ;; - _initialize: Runtime initialization
  (list
   ;; Compile form function - first user function after FFI imports
   '("compile_form" #x00 4)   ; kind=func, index=4 (after 4 FFI imports)
   ;; Compile all function
   '("compile_all" #x00 5)    ; kind=func, index=5
   ;; Initialize function
   '("_initialize" #x00 6)))  ; kind=func, index=6

;;; ============================================================
;;; Export Index Tracking
;;; ============================================================

(defvar *next-export-index* 4
  "Next available function index for exports (after FFI imports)")

(defun allocate-export-index ()
  "Allocate next export index"
  (prog1 *next-export-index*
    (incf *next-export-index*)))

(defun reset-export-indices ()
  "Reset export index allocation"
  (setf *next-export-index* 4))

   153→(defun read-source-file (path)

   155→   Returns a list of S-expressions."
   156→  (with-open-file (stream path :direction :input
   157→                               :external-format :utf-8)
   158→    (let ((forms '())
   159→          (eof (gensym "EOF")))

   161→            until (eq form eof)
   162→            do (push form forms))

   165→(defun read-all-source-forms (&optional (base-dir (asdf:system-source-directory :clysm)))

   167→   Returns a flat list of all S-expressions."
   168→  (let ((all-forms '()))
   169→    (dolist (relative-path *compilation-order*)
   170→      (let ((full-path (merge-pathnames relative-path base-dir)))
   171→        (when (probe-file full-path)

   182→   Excludes: in-package, defpackage, declare, proclaim, eval-when.
   183→   Also excludes: (defun (setf ...) ...) forms (not yet supported)."
   184→  (and (consp form)
   185→       (symbolp (car form))
   186→       (member (car form)
   187→               '(;; Definitions
   188→                 defun defmacro defvar defparameter defconstant
   189→                 defstruct defclass defgeneric defmethod
   190→                 deftype define-condition define-compiler-macro
   191→                 define-symbol-macro define-setf-expander
   192→                 define-modify-macro define-method-combination
   193→                 ;; Control structures
   194→                 progn let let* flet labels block tagbody
   195→                 lambda setf setq if when unless cond case typecase
   196→                 ;; Package operations (these are compile-time side effects)
   197→                 export)
   198→               :test #'eq)
   199→       ;; Exclude (defun (setf foo) ...) forms - not yet supported
   200→       (not (and (eq (car form) 'defun)
   201→                 (consp (cadr form))

   204→(defun filter-compilable-forms (forms)

   209→;;; ============================================================
   210→;;; Selective Macro Pre-Expansion
   211→;;; ============================================================

   213→;; We need to expand certain CL macros (case, cond, when, unless) because

   215→;; (defstruct, etypecase) that require runtime type info.
   216→
   217→(defparameter *skip-expansion-ops*

   219→    etypecase typecase ecase ctypecase ccase check-type
   220→    ;; Condition handling - complex expansions
   221→    handler-case handler-bind restart-case restart-bind
   222→    with-simple-restart ignore-errors
   223→    ;; Note: defstruct is now handled by expand-form-recursive (Feature 038)

   226→    ;; Variable/constant definitions - don't expand to SBCL internals (Feature 038)

   228→    ;; Quote and function - don't expand contents
   229→    quote function)
   230→  "Operators whose macro expansion should be skipped.")

   233→  '(;; These expand to simple if/cond forms universally
   234→    case when unless
   235→    and or
   236→    ;; Simple control flow
   237→    prog1 prog2
   238→    ;; Feature 043: Binding macros - SBCL expands to let/mvb
   239→    multiple-value-bind)

   241→   Note: LOOP/DO macros are NOT expanded here because SBCL expands
   242→   them to SBCL-internal functions. Instead, Clysm's macro system
   243→   (registered in clysm/lib/macros.lisp) handles them.")
   244→
   245→(defun expand-form-recursive (form)
   246→  "Recursively expand select macros in FORM.
   247→   Expands case/cond/when/unless but skips defstruct/etypecase/etc."
   248→  (cond
   249→    ;; Atoms and nil - pass through
   250→    ((atom form) form)
   251→    ((null form) nil)
   252→    ;; Skip these ops entirely (including their subforms)
   253→    ((and (consp form)
   254→          (symbolp (car form))
   255→          (member (car form) *skip-expansion-ops*))
   256→     form)
   257→    ;; Must-expand ops - use SBCL to expand
   258→    ((and (consp form)
   259→          (symbolp (car form))
   260→          (member (car form) *must-expand-ops*))
   261→     (handler-case
   262→         (let ((expanded (macroexpand-1 form)))
   263→           (if (equal expanded form)
   264→               ;; No expansion happened - recurse into subforms
   265→               (cons (car form)
   266→                     (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cdr form)))
   267→               ;; Expansion happened - recurse on result
   268→               (expand-form-recursive expanded)))
   269→       (error (e)
   270→         (format *error-output* "~%Warning: Error expanding ~A: ~A~%"
   271→                 (car form) e)
   272→         form)))
   273→    ;; defmacro - keep body unexpanded
   274→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'defmacro))
   275→     form)
   276→    ;; Feature 038: define-condition - expand to defclass
   277→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'define-condition))
   278→     (expand-form-recursive (expand-define-condition form)))
   279→    ;; Feature 038: defstruct - expand to constructor/accessor defuns
   280→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'defstruct))
   281→     (let ((defuns (expand-defstruct form)))
   282→       ;; Return a progn of all generated defuns
   283→       (cons 'progn (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive defuns))))
   284→    ;; defun - expand body forms
   285→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'defun))
   286→     (list* 'defun
   287→            (cadr form)   ; name
   288→            (caddr form)  ; params
   289→            (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cdddr form))))
   290→    ;; let/let* - expand binding values and body
   291→    ((and (consp form) (member (car form) '(let let*)))
   292→     (list* (car form)
   293→            (mapcar (lambda (binding)
   294→                      (if (consp binding)
   295→                          (list (car binding)
   296→                                (expand-form-recursive (cadr binding)))
   297→                          binding))
   298→                    (cadr form))
   299→            (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cddr form))))
   300→    ;; flet/labels - expand function bodies
   301→    ((and (consp form) (member (car form) '(flet labels)))
   302→     (list* (car form)
   303→            (mapcar (lambda (def)
   304→                      (list* (car def)   ; name
   305→                             (cadr def)  ; params
   306→                             (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cddr def))))
   307→                    (cadr form))
   308→            (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cddr form))))
   309→    ;; lambda - expand body
   310→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'lambda))
   311→     (list* 'lambda
   312→            (cadr form)  ; params
   313→            (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cddr form))))
   314→    ;; block - expand body
   315→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'block))
   316→     (list* 'block
   317→            (cadr form)  ; name
   318→            (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cddr form))))
   319→    ;; progn - expand all forms
   320→    ((and (consp form) (eq (car form) 'progn))
   321→     (cons 'progn (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cdr form))))
   322→    ;; General compound form - try to expand if it's a macro
   323→    ((consp form)
   324→     (handler-case
   325→         (multiple-value-bind (expanded expanded-p)
   326→             (macroexpand-1 form)
   327→           (if expanded-p
   328→               (expand-form-recursive expanded)
   329→               ;; Not a macro - just recurse into subforms
   330→               (cons (car form)
   331→                     (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive (cdr form)))))
   332→       (error (e)
   333→         (format *error-output* "~%Warning: Error expanding ~A: ~A~%"
   334→                 (if (consp form) (car form) form) e)
   335→         form)))
   336→    ;; Fallback
   337→    (t form)))
   338→
   339→(defun expand-all-forms (forms)
   340→  "Selectively expand macros in FORMS."
   341→  (mapcar #'expand-form-recursive forms))

   369→            (format *error-output* "ERROR reading ~A: ~A~%" full-path e)
   370→            (return-from collect-all-forms nil)))))
   371→    ;; Selectively expand macros (case, cond, when, unless, etc.)
   372→    ;; while skipping ones that need runtime type info (defstruct, etypecase)
   373→    (format t "~%Expanding macros...~%")
   374→    (handler-case
   375→        (let ((expanded (expand-all-forms all-forms)))
   376→          (setf (bootstrap-context-all-forms ctx) expanded)
   377→          expanded)
   378→      (error (e)
   379→        (setf (bootstrap-context-error-info ctx)
   380→              (list "macro-expansion" (format nil "~A" e) nil))
   381→        (format *error-output* "ERROR during macro expansion: ~A~%" e)
   382→        nil))))
   383→
   384→;;; ============================================================
   385→;;; T017: Compile All Forms
   386→;;; ============================================================
   387→
   388→(defstruct compile-result
   389→  "Result of compilation attempt."
   390→  (successful 0 :type fixnum)      ; Count of successfully compiled forms
   391→  (failed 0 :type fixnum)          ; Count of failed forms
   392→  (failed-forms nil :type list)    ; List of (form . error) for failures
   393→  (bytes nil)                      ; Final Wasm bytes
   394→  ;; Feature 038: Enhanced Error Reporting
   395→  (operator-failures (make-hash-table :test 'eq) :type hash-table)  ; Operator → count
   396→  (operator-examples (make-hash-table :test 'eq) :type hash-table)) ; Operator → list of form strings
   397→
   398→;;; ============================================================
   399→;;; Feature 038 T053-T063: Enhanced Error Reporting
   400→;;; ============================================================
   401→
   402→(defun record-failure (form error result)
   403→  "Record a compilation failure in RESULT, tracking by operator type.
   404→   FORM is the failed form, ERROR is the condition, RESULT is compile-result."
   405→  (let* ((op (if (consp form) (car form) 'atom))
   406→         (failures (compile-result-operator-failures result))
   407→         (examples (compile-result-operator-examples result)))
   408→    ;; Increment failure count for this operator
   409→    (incf (gethash op failures 0))
   410→    (incf (compile-result-failed result))
   411→    ;; Store up to 3 examples per operator
   412→    (let ((existing (gethash op examples)))
   413→      (when (< (length existing) 3)
   414→        (let ((form-preview (format nil "~A" form)))
   415→          (when (> (length form-preview) 100)
   416→            (setf form-preview (concatenate 'string
   417→                                            (subseq form-preview 0 97)
   418→                                            "...")))
   419→          (setf (gethash op examples)
   420→                (append existing (list form-preview))))))))
   421→
   422→(defun generate-failure-report (result stream)
   423→  "Generate an operator-grouped failure report to STREAM.
   424→   Shows compilation rate, failures by operator, and examples."
   425→  (let* ((successful (compile-result-successful result))
   426→         (failed (compile-result-failed result))
   427→         (total (+ successful failed))
   428→         (rate (if (zerop total) 0.0 (* 100.0 (/ successful total)))))
   429→    ;; Summary line
   430→    (format stream "~%Compilation Summary: ~D/~D forms compiled (~,1F%)~%~%"
   431→            successful total rate)
   432→
   433→    ;; Failures by operator (sorted by count descending)
   434→    (let ((failures (compile-result-operator-failures result))
   435→          (examples (compile-result-operator-examples result))
   436→          (sorted-ops '()))
   437→      ;; Collect and sort operators by failure count
   438→      (maphash (lambda (op count)
   439→                 (push (cons op count) sorted-ops))
   440→               failures)
   441→      (setf sorted-ops (sort sorted-ops #'> :key #'cdr))
   442→
   443→      (when sorted-ops
   444→        (format stream "Failures by operator:~%")
   445→        (dolist (pair sorted-ops)
   446→          (let ((op (car pair))
   447→                (count (cdr pair)))
   448→            (format stream "  ~A: ~D failures~%" op count)
   449→            ;; Show examples for this operator
   450→            (let ((op-examples (gethash op examples)))
   451→              (dolist (ex op-examples)
   452→                (format stream "    - ~A~%" ex)))))
   453→        (format stream "~%")))))
   454→
   455→;;; ============================================================
   456→;;; Feature 038 T034-T039, T070-T079: Form Expansion Stubs
   457→;;; (Full implementation in Phase 4/US2 and Phase 7/US5)
   458→;;; ============================================================
   459→
   460→(defun expand-define-condition (form)
   461→  "Expand define-condition to defclass form.
   462→   FORM: (define-condition name parents slots . options)
   463→   Returns: (defclass name parents slots . filtered-options)
   464→   Note: :report option is skipped (not passed to defclass)."
   465→  (destructuring-bind (op name parents slots &rest options) form
   466→    (declare (ignore op))
   467→    ;; Filter out :report option as it's not a defclass option
   468→    (let ((filtered-options (remove-if (lambda (opt)
   469→                                          (and (consp opt)
   470→                                               (eq (car opt) :report)))
   471→                                        options)))
   472→      (list* 'defclass name parents slots filtered-options))))
   473→
   474→(defun expand-defstruct (form)
   475→  "Expand defstruct to constructor and accessor defuns.
   476→   FORM: (defstruct name-and-options [docstring] slot1 slot2 ...)
   477→   Returns: list of defun forms (make-NAME, NAME-slot, NAME-p)."
   478→  (let* ((name-and-options (cadr form))
   479→         (name (if (consp name-and-options)
   480→                   (car name-and-options)
   481→                   name-and-options))
   482→         (options (when (consp name-and-options)
   483→                    (cdr name-and-options)))
   484→         (body (cddr form))
   485→         ;; Skip docstring if present (first element is a string)
   486→         (slots (if (and (consp body) (stringp (car body)))
   487→                    (cdr body)
   488→                    body))
   489→         ;; Extract :constructor option if present
   490→         (constructor-opt (find :constructor options :key (lambda (x)
   491→                                                             (when (consp x)
   492→                                                               (car x)))))
   493→         (constructor-name (if constructor-opt
   494→                               (cadr constructor-opt)
   495→                               (intern (format nil "MAKE-~A" name))))
   496→         (predicate-name (intern (format nil "~A-P" name)))
   497→         (result '()))
   498→
   499→    ;; Parse slots: each slot can be SYMBOL or (SYMBOL DEFAULT)
   500→    ;; Note: We extract slot names only - defaults are handled by nil-or-default
   501→    ;; pattern in constructor body because Clysm doesn't support &key with defaults.
   502→    (let ((slot-specs (mapcar (lambda (slot)
   503→                                (if (consp slot)
   504→                                    (list (car slot) (cadr slot))
   505→                                    (list slot nil)))
   506→                              slots)))
   507→
   508→      ;; Generate constructor - use simple &key without defaults (Clysm limitation)
   509→      ;; Defaults are applied in the body using (if x x default) pattern
   510→      (let* ((slot-names (mapcar #'car slot-specs))
   511→             (lambda-list `(&key ,@slot-names)))
   512→        (push `(defun ,constructor-name ,lambda-list
   513→                 (list ',name
   514→                       ,@(mapcar (lambda (spec)
   515→                                   (let ((name (car spec))
   516→                                         (default (cadr spec)))
   517→                                     (if default
   518→                                         `(if ,name ,name ,default)
   519→                                         name)))
   520→                                 slot-specs)))
   521→              result))
   522→
   523→      ;; Generate accessors
   524→      (loop for spec in slot-specs
   525→            for index from 1
   526→            for slot-name = (car spec)
   527→            for accessor-name = (intern (format nil "~A-~A" name slot-name))
   528→            do (push `(defun ,accessor-name (struct)
   529→                        (nth ,index struct))
   530→                     result))
   531→
   532→      ;; Generate predicate
   533→      (push `(defun ,predicate-name (obj)
   534→               (and (consp obj)
   535→                    (eq (car obj) ',name)))
   536→            result))
   537→
   538→    (nreverse result)))
   539→
   540→(defun try-compile-form (form compile-fn)
   541→  "Try to compile a single form. Returns (values bytes error)."
   542→  (handler-case
   543→      (values (funcall compile-fn form) nil)
   544→    (error (e)
   545→      (values nil e))))
   546→
   547→(defun compile-all-forms (forms)
   548→  "Compile forms to Wasm, trying each individually and tracking failures.
   549→   Returns a COMPILE-RESULT struct with statistics and bytes."
   550→  (let* ((compile-fn (uiop:find-symbol* :compile-to-wasm :clysm/compiler))
   551→         (result (make-compile-result))
   552→         (compilable-forms '()))
   553→
   554→    ;; First pass: try each form individually to see what compiles
   555→    (format t "Testing individual forms...~%")
   556→    (loop for form in forms
   557→          for i from 0
   558→          do (multiple-value-bind (bytes err)
   559→                 (try-compile-form form compile-fn)
   560→               (declare (ignore bytes))
   561→               (if err
   562→                   ;; Use record-failure for operator-grouped tracking
   563→                   (progn
   564→                     (record-failure form err result)
   565→                     (push (cons form err) (compile-result-failed-forms result)))
   566→                   (progn
   567→                     (incf (compile-result-successful result))
   568→                     (push form compilable-forms)))))
   569→
   570→    (setf compilable-forms (nreverse compilable-forms))
   571→    (setf (compile-result-failed-forms result)
   572→          (nreverse (compile-result-failed-forms result)))
   573→
   574→    (format t "~%Results: ~D compiled, ~D failed~%"
   575→            (compile-result-successful result)
   576→            (compile-result-failed result))
   577→
   578→    ;; Feature 038: Generate operator-grouped failure report
   579→    (generate-failure-report result *standard-output*)
   580→
   581→    ;; Second pass: compile all successful forms together
   582→    (if (null compilable-forms)
   583→        ;; No forms compiled - generate minimal valid Wasm module
   584→        (progn
   585→          (format t "~%Generating minimal Wasm module (no compilable forms)~%")
   586→          (setf (compile-result-bytes result)
   587→                (generate-minimal-wasm-module)))
   588→        ;; Compile successful forms into single module
   589→        (progn
   590→          (format t "~%Compiling ~D forms to single module...~%"
   591→                  (length compilable-forms))
   592→          (let ((expr (if (= 1 (length compilable-forms))
   593→                          (first compilable-forms)
   594→                          `(progn ,@compilable-forms))))
   595→            (handler-case
   596→                (setf (compile-result-bytes result)
   597→                      (funcall compile-fn expr))
   598→              (error (e)
   599→                ;; Even combined compilation failed - use minimal module
   600→                (format t "~%Combined compilation failed: ~A~%" e)
   601→                (format t "Generating minimal Wasm module~%")
   602→                (setf (compile-result-bytes result)
   603→                      (generate-minimal-wasm-module)))))))
   604→
   605→    result))
   606→
   607→(defun generate-minimal-wasm-module ()
   608→  "Generate a minimal valid Wasm module (empty module).
   609→   Magic number: 0x00 0x61 0x73 0x6D (\\0asm)
   610→   Version: 0x01 0x00 0x00 0x00 (1)"
   611→  (make-array 8 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   612→              :initial-contents '(#x00 #x61 #x73 #x6D  ; magic
   613→                                  #x01 #x00 #x00 #x00)))
   614→
   615→;;; ============================================================
   616→;;; T018: Write Wasm Output
   617→;;; ============================================================
   618→
   619→(defun write-wasm-output (bytes output-path)
   620→  "Write Wasm binary to output file.
   621→   Returns the pathname."
   622→  (ensure-directories-exist output-path)
   623→  (with-open-file (stream output-path
   624→                          :direction :output
   625→                          :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   626→                          :if-exists :supersede)
   627→    (write-sequence bytes stream))
   628→  (pathname output-path))
   629→
   630→;;; ============================================================
   631→;;; T022: Validate Output
   632→;;; ============================================================
   633→
   634→(defun validate-output (output-path)
   635→  "Validate the output Wasm binary using wasm-tools.
   636→   Returns (values success-p error-message)."
   637→  (multiple-value-bind (output error-output exit-code)
   638→      (uiop:run-program (list "wasm-tools" "validate" (namestring output-path))
   639→                        :output :string
   640→                        :error-output :string
   641→                        :ignore-error-status t)
   642→    (declare (ignore output))
   643→    (if (zerop exit-code)
   644→        (values t nil)
   645→        (values nil error-output))))
   646→
   647→;;; ============================================================
   648→;;; T019-T021: Run Bootstrap (Main Entry Point)
   649→;;; ============================================================
   650→
   651→(defun run-bootstrap (&key (output-path "dist/clysm-stage0.wasm"))
   652→  "Main entry point for Stage 0 bootstrap compilation.
   653→   Compiles all 41 modules and produces a single Wasm binary."
   654→  (let* ((ctx (make-bootstrap-context :output-path output-path))
   655→         (start-time (get-internal-real-time)))
   656→    (setf (bootstrap-context-compilation-start ctx) start-time)
   657→
   658→    (format t "~%=== Clysm Stage 0 Bootstrap ===~%~%")
   659→    (format t "Output: ~A~%" output-path)
   660→    (format t "Modules: ~D~%~%" (length *compilation-order*))
   661→
   662→    ;; Collect all forms
   663→    (format t "Phase 1: Reading source modules...~%")
   664→    (let ((forms (collect-all-forms ctx)))
   665→      (when (null forms)
   666→        (format *error-output* "~%Bootstrap FAILED: Could not read source forms~%")
   667→        (return-from run-bootstrap nil))
   668→
   669→      (format t "~%Collected ~D compilable forms~%~%" (length forms))
   670→
   671→      ;; Compile all forms
   672→      (format t "Phase 2: Compiling to Wasm...~%")
   673→      (handler-case
   674→          (let ((result (compile-all-forms forms)))
   675→            ;; Write output
   676→            (format t "~%Phase 3: Writing output...~%")
   677→            (write-wasm-output (compile-result-bytes result) output-path)
   678→
   679→            ;; T020-T021: Timing and size reporting
   680→            (let* ((end-time (get-internal-real-time))
   681→                   (duration-secs (/ (- end-time start-time)
   682→                                     internal-time-units-per-second))
   683→                   (size-bytes (length (compile-result-bytes result))))
   684→              (format t "~%=== Bootstrap Complete ===~%~%")
   685→              (format t "Output: ~A~%" output-path)
   686→              (format t "Size: ~:D bytes~%" size-bytes)
   687→              (format t "Duration: ~,2F seconds~%~%" duration-secs)
   688→
   689→              ;; Compilation statistics
   690→              (format t "Compilation Statistics:~%")
   691→              (format t "  Successfully compiled: ~D forms~%"
   692→                      (compile-result-successful result))
   693→              (format t "  Failed to compile: ~D forms~%~%"
   694→                      (compile-result-failed result))
   695→
   696→              ;; Validate output
   697→              (format t "Phase 4: Validating Wasm...~%")
   698→              (multiple-value-bind (valid-p error-msg)
   699→                  (validate-output output-path)
   700→                (if valid-p
   701→                    (format t "Validation: PASSED~%~%")
   702→                    (format t "Validation: FAILED - ~A~%~%" error-msg)))
   703→
   704→              output-path))
   705→        (error (e)
   706→          (setf (bootstrap-context-error-info ctx)
   707→                (list (bootstrap-context-current-module ctx)
   708→                      (format nil "~A" e)
   709→                      nil))
   710→          (format *error-output* "~%Bootstrap FAILED during compilation:~%~A~%" e)
   711→          nil)))))
   712→
   713→;;; ============================================================
   714→;;; Auto-run when loaded
   715→;;; ============================================================
   716→
   717→;; Load Clysm system first
   718→(unless (find-package :clysm/compiler)
   719→  (format t "Loading Clysm compiler...~%")
   720→  ;; Use load-source-op to avoid compilation issues with ASDF treating warnings as errors
   721→  ;; This is slower but more robust for bootstrap
   722→  (handler-case
   723→      (asdf:load-system :clysm)
   724→    (error (e)
   725→      (format t "Warning: ASDF compile failed (~A), trying source load...~%" e)
   726→      (asdf:oos 'asdf:load-source-op :clysm))))
   727→
   728→;; Feature 043: Initialize the global macro registry with standard macros
   729→;; This is critical - without this, LOOP and other macros are not expanded!
   730→(clysm/lib/macros:install-standard-macros
   731→ (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:global-macro-registry))
   732→(format t "Initialized standard macros (LOOP, DO, WHEN, UNLESS, etc.)~%")
   733→
   734→;; Run bootstrap if this file is loaded directly
   735→(when (and (boundp '*load-pathname*)
   736→           *load-pathname*
   737→           (string= "bootstrap" (pathname-name *load-pathname*)))
   738→  (run-bootstrap))
   739→
